{"type":"message","id":"ac02e2ea","parentId":"d7dc4f3f","timestamp":"2026-05-27T04:08:54.767Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I can see the readable strings. Let me find the \"GitPull\" section specifically to see what steps/pipelines include it. I can see:\n\n- `GitPull` - appears as a step\n- `Git` - appears near it\n- `PipelineHotUpdate` - the hot update pipeline\n\nAlso I see CDN-related strings:\n- `http://192.168.95.85/cdn_solo/` - CDN path\n- `D:/cdn_solo` - local CDN path\n- `PipelineBuildCDNPackageOpen` - CDN related step\n- `PipelineBuildCDNPackageOpenTogether`\n- `PipelineBuildCDNPackageWhiteVersion` etc.\n\nBut I need to understand the structure better. The binary format is a custom Unity binary serializer. Let me see if I can find the actual steps/configuration entries.\n\nLet me look at the raw binary more carefully to find the step configurations, especially the \"GitPull\" step and whether it's checked/unchecked.\n\nActually, this is a binary serialized format. Let me look at the readable strings more carefully. I found:\n\n- `GitPull` - this is a step name\n- `Git` - a category/type\n- `PipelineHotUpdate` - the pipeline name\n\nAnd from the pipeline name perspective:\n- `PipelineCheck`\n- `PipelineBuild`\n- `PipelineUndoChange`\n- `PipelinePlayerSetting`\n- `PipelineBuildAssetBundle`\n- `PipelineHotUpdate`\n- `PipelineBuildCDNPackageOpen`\n- etc.\n\nThe key question is: has the GitPull step been unchecked/disabled? The binary format might use booleans or flags to indicate enabled/disabled state.\n\nLet me try to parse the file more carefully. But this is a custom Unity binary format (probably `BinaryFormatter` or Unity's own serialization), so it's hard to interpret programmatically.\n\nLet me try to see the hex dump around the \"GitPull\" string to understand its context.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_LRtI4Vuj51rt0rF1JrcI3199","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\scripts\\read_buildpipe_config2.mjs","content":"import fs from 'fs';\n\nconst b = fs.readFileSync('E:/Solo/nightoffullmoon/client/cardv/Assets/EditorConfig/BuildPipelineConfig.bytes');\n\n// Find \"GitPull\" and show surrounding bytes\nconst gitPullStr = 'GitPull';\nconst gitPullIndex = b.indexOf(Buffer.from(gitPullStr, 'utf8'));\nconsole.log('=== GitPull found at offset:', gitPullIndex, '===');\nconsole.log('Surrounding 80 bytes (hex):');\nconst start = Math.max(0, gitPullIndex - 40);\nconst end = Math.min(b.length, gitPullIndex + 40);\nfor (let i = start; i < end; i++) {\n  process.stdout.write(b[i].toString(16).padStart(2, '0') + ' ');\n}\nconsole.log('\\n\\nSurrounding text:');\nlet text = '';\nfor (let i = start; i < end; i++) {\n  let ch = b[i];\n  text += (ch >= 32 && ch <= 126) ? String.fromCharCode(ch) : '.';\n}\nconsole.log(text);\n\n// Also find \"Git\" step related patterns\nconsole.log('\\n\\n=== Searching for pipeline step entries ===');\n// Look for patterns that might indicate enabled/disabled state\nconst patterns = ['PipelineHotUpdate', 'PipelineBuildAssetBundle', 'PipelinePlayerSetting', 'PipelineCheck', 'GitPull', 'Git'];\nfor (const pat of patterns) {\n  const idx = b.indexOf(Buffer.from(pat, 'utf8'));\n  if (idx >= 0) {\n    console.log(`\\n\"${pat}\" at offset ${idx}:`);\n    const s = Math.max(0, idx - 20);\n    const e = Math.min(b.length, idx + 50);\n    let line = '';\n    for (let i = s; i < e; i++) {\n      let ch = b[i];\n      line += (ch >= 32 && ch <= 126) ? String.fromCharCode(ch) : '.';\n    }\n    console.log(`  Context: ${line}`);\n    console.log(`  Hex: ` + Array.from(b.subarray(s, e)).map(x => x.toString(16).padStart(2,'0')).join(' '));\n  }\n}\n\n// Let's look at the overall structure - scan for 0x00 0x01 pattern (bool true) and 0x00 0x00 (bool false)\nconsole.log('\\n\\n=== Looking for boolean patterns near known strings ===');\n// Find all strings and look at bytes before th