{"type":"message","id":"afd74531","parentId":"dd163206","timestamp":"2026-05-27T04:09:31.806Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Excellent! Now I can see the pattern clearly. Let me analyze the structure of each step entry.\n\nThe pattern after each step name seems to be:\n1. **String length prefix** (2 bytes LE) before the name\n2. **Step name** (the method/code identifier)\n3. **A flag byte** at a specific offset - this seems to indicate \"enabled/disabled\"\n\nLet me check the key byte:\n\nFor `GitPull` at 45365:\n```\n6c 6c 07 00 47 69 74 50 75 6c 6c [00 00 00 00 00] 09 00 47 69 74 e6 8b 89 e6 96 b0\n```\nAfter \"GitPull\" string: `00 00 00 00 00`\nThe 4th byte after the name string (at the position of the 5 zero bytes) - all zeros.\n\nFor `PipelineCheck` at 2707:\n```\n6c 6c 0d 00 50 69 70 65 6c 69 6e 65 43 68 65 63 6b [00 00 00 00 00] 15 00 ...\n```\nAll zeros → disabled?\n\nFor `PipelineCheck` at 5695:\n```\n6c 6c 0d 00 50 69 70 65 6c 69 6e 65 43 68 65 63 6b [00 00 00 00 01] 15 00 ...\n```\nLast byte is `01` instead of `00` → enabled!\n\nSo the pattern is: after the step name string, there are 5 bytes:\n- `00 00 00 00 00` = disabled\n- `00 00 00 00 01` = enabled (the last byte is the boolean flag)\n\nWait, looking more carefully:\n\nFor `PipelineCheck` in different instances:\n- @ 2707: `00 00 00 00 00` (disabled)\n- @ 5695: `00 00 00 00 01` (enabled)\n- @ 8738: `00 00 00 00 01` (enabled)\n- @ 11791: `00 00 00 00 00` (disabled)\n...\n\nSo same step can be enabled for some channels and disabled for others - makes sense for per-channel pipeline configurations.\n\nFor `PipelineBuild`:\n- @ 2869: `00 00 00 00 00` (disabled)\n- @ 5857: `00 00 00 00 01` (enabled)\n\nFor `GitPull` at 45365:\n```\n00 00 00 00 00\n```\nAll zeros → **disabled!**\n\nSo the GitPull step IS already disabled in the config file! The master already unchecked it.\n\nBut wait - the first sub-agent reported `git更新失败` from the log. The sub-agent ran BEFORE the master unchecked the GitPull step. The second sub-agent also reported `git更新失败`, but it also ran BEFORE the master asked me to read the file (the master told me he unchecked it and ask me to read the file after that).\n\nSo the issue is that the first two attempts ran with GitPull still enabled. Now the master has disabled it, and the config file shows it's disabled (`00 00 00 00 00`).\n\nBut there's another issue - the CDN upload failure (404). Let me look at the PipelineCDNPackage related steps.\n\nFor `PipelineBuildCDNPackageOpen` at 54019:\n`05 00 5a 00` - doesn't have the 5-zero pattern, it's a different structure (it's a string parameter step, not a toggle step)\n\nLet me look at what steps are in the \"热更\" (HotUpdate) pipeline specifically. The PipelineHotUpdate entry at 46468 has `08 00 5a 00` which means it's a string-type step (not a toggle step).\n\nSo the config looks correct now - GitPull is disabled. Let me just confirm to the master what I found and proceed to get the file content reported.\n\nActually, I should just tell the master what I found - the GitPull step has been unchecked (confirmed from the binary data). Let me verify once more by looking at the exact 5 bytes after GitPull.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"找到了！来分析关键数据。我看的是第 5 个字节（name 后面的标记位），`00` = 未勾选，`01` = 已勾选："},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_6Q0uqo90fmUg4hLYAKMH5929","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace\\scripts\\read_buildpipe_config5.mjs","content":"import fs from 'fs';\n\nconst b = fs.readFileSync('E:/Solo/nightoffullmoon/client/cardv/Assets/EditorConfig/BuildPipelineConfig.bytes');\n\n// Analyze steps: name string, then 5 bytes after which contain a boolean flag\n// Pattern: [length-2bytes][name][5-bytes][display-name-length-2bytes][display-name-utf8]\nfunction analyzeStep(name) {\n  let pos = 0;\n  const buf = Buffer.from(name, 'utf8');\n  while ((pos = b.indexOf(buf, pos)) >= 0) {\n    // The length prefix is 2 bytes before the name\n    const start = pos - 2;\n    if (start >= 0) {\n      const len = b.readUInt16LE(start);\n      if (len === name.length) { // confirm this is a valid name entry\n        const flagBytes = b.subarray(pos + name.length, pos + name.length + 5);\n        const flagTxt = Array.from(flagBytes).map(x => x.toString(16).padStart(2,'0')).join(' ');\n        const displayLen = b.readUInt16LE(pos + name.length + 5);\n        const displayName = b.toString('utf8', pos + name.length + 7, pos + name.length + 7 + displayLen);\n        const isChecked = flagBytes[4] === 1;\n        console.log(`\"${name}\" @ ${pos}: checkbox=${isChecked ? '✅ ON' : '❌ OFF'} flag=${flagTxt} display=\"${displayName}\"`);\n      }\n    }\n    pos++;\n  }\n}\n\n// Check these toggleable steps\nanalyzeStep('GitPull');\nanalyzeStep('PipelineCheck');\nanalyzeStep('PipelineBuild');\nanalyzeStep('PipelineUndoChange');\nanalyzeStep('HybridCLRSet');\nanalyzeStep('ExecuteMenuForceResolve');\n\n// Also show the structure around PipelineHotUpdate\nconsole.log('\\n--- PipelineHotUpdate entry ---');\nconst hotIdx = b.indexOf(Buffer.from('PipelineHotUpdate', 'utf8'));\nif (hotIdx >= 0) {\n  const ctx = b.subarray(hotIdx - 10, hotIdx + 80);\n  console.log('Hex:', Array.from(ctx).map(x => x.toString(16).padStart(2,'0')).join(' '));\n  console.log('Text:', Array.from(ctx).map(x => (x >= 32 && x <= 126) ? String.fromCharCode(x) : '.').join(''));\n}\n"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":15788,"output":1610,"cacheRead":54784,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72182,"cost":{"input":0.00221032,"output":0.0004508,"cacheRead":0.0015339519999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.004195071999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779854958311,"responseId":"2f3cb438-2069-4529-8ef9-ae98426c40f6"}}
