{"type":"message","id":"f35e2ed8","parentId":"83a82e25","timestamp":"2026-05-27T05:13:03.786Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The third attempt also failed. The GitPull step was unchecked in the config, but `PullBattleModuleForce()` was still called - this means the method is being called from somewhere else in the pipeline, not just from the GitPull toggle step. \n\nLet me look at the log to understand what's happening. The sub-agent said the GitPull step was still executed even though it's unchecked. This might mean:\n1. The `GitPull()` method is embedded in another step\n2. The config change didn't take effect (maybe Unity needs to re-read the config?)\n3. There's something else calling `PullBattleModuleForce()`\n\nLet me look at the actual log file to see the full error context and understand the flow better.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_FsCfNWJVZkP1bILtV21U5585","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"powershell -Command \"Select-String -Path 'E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\BuildPipeline_RunHotUpdate.log' -Pattern 'git更新失败|GitPull|PullBattleModuleForce' -Context 2,5\"","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":31913,"output":267,"cacheRead":37120,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":69300,"cost":{"input":0.00446782,"output":0.00007476000000000001,"cacheRead":0.00103936,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0055819400000000005}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779858779206,"responseId":"b5747c89-45de-4256-ac27-8c0f3e8ae1a8"}}
