{"type":"message","id":"1773a2a8","parentId":"8fac52c9","timestamp":"2026-05-27T05:13:10.756Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So even though the GitPull step was unchecked in the config, the `GitPull()` method is still being called! Let me look at the source code of `BuildPipelineMethod_Utility.cs` to understand why.\n\nLooking at the stack trace:\n1. `BuildPipeline.cs:ExecuteStep` is calling `GitPull()` method\n2. `GitPull()` at line 283 logs something\n3. Then at line 327-332, GitPull calls `EditorTools.PullBattleModuleForce()` \n4. Inside PullBattleModuleForce, the actual `git pull` fails\n\nThe issue is that the config unchecked the step, but `GitPull()` is still being invoked in the pipeline execution. This means either:\n1. The config file wasn't saved/reloaded properly\n2. There's a different pipeline configuration being used\n3. The `BuildPipeline.ExecuteStep` is still finding the step despite the checkbox being off\n\nLet me look at the source code to understand how the pipeline determines if a step should be skipped.\n\nActually, looking at line 440 - `BuildPipelineMethod:GitPull() (at Assets/Editor/BuildPipeline/Method/BuildPipelineMethod_Utility.cs:283)` - this is the first GitPull call. Then line 580 at `EditorTools.cs:121` calls `PullFrameworkModule` which is another pull.\n\nSo the GitPull step IS being executed even though it's unchecked! Let me look at the source code to understand how the pipeline decides which steps to run.\n\nLet me check the BuildPipeline.cs to see the ExecuteStep logic.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"看来取消勾选没有生效，`GitPull()` 仍然被调用了。看看源码是怎么回事："},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_2fdST9hNQwwo0DKEE5hs5156","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\client\\cardv\\Assets\\Editor\\BuildPipeline\\BuildPipeline.cs","offset":220,"limit":60}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":3213,"outpu